cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.CR

The paper proposes a framework for predictive process monitoring using clustering and classification techniques. This involves analyzing event logs and data attributes associated with events to predict the probability of a given predicate being fulfilled upon completion of a running case. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves building classifiers to discriminate between fulfillments and violations. The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework in the ProM toolset, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) tool for process mining. Additionally, the use of event logs and data attributes involves database (cs.DB) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the framework on a log pertaining to the treatment of cancer patients, which involves security and cryptography (cs.CR) concerns.
